      "name": "Fresh thyme",
      "amount": "1 sprig",
      "notes": "chopped"
    }
  ],
  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the oven to 375°F (190°C).",
    "Cook the bacon in a large skillet over medium heat until crispy, then set aside.",
    "Sauté the leeks in the same skillet until softened.",
    "Add the garlic and cook for 1 minute.",
    "Combine the cooked leeks, garlic, and bacon in a large cazuela or baking dish.",
    "Top with sliced Emmentaler cheese and chopped fresh parsley.",
    "Season with salt, black pepper, and chopped fresh thyme.",
    "Cover the dish with a sheet of parchment paper or aluminum foil and bake for 20 minutes.",
    "Remove the parchment paper or foil and continue baking for an additional 10-15 minutes, or until the cheese is melted and golden-brown.",
    "Serve hot and enjoy!"
  ],
